'''Coruscant Charm Signing''' was a method of giving out signs and intent. Much like the [[Language/Legends|language]] of flowers, where giving the precise flower, number and arrangement has a specific meaning.

It was confined to the social class of [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] officer trainees from wealthy families and their circles. The practice came out of [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]] long before the rise of the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Empire]].

During a party thrown in honor of [[Wraith Squadron]] [[Pilot/Legends|pilots]] [[Wes Janson/Legends|Wes Janson]] and [[Hohass Ekwesh]]'s recovery, [[Gara Petothel|Lara Notsil]] gave a sign to fellow Wraith [[Myn Donos]] that said ''I'd accept a kiss'' which he didn't understand. However, [[Garik Loran|Face Loran]], a former [[Actor/Legends|actor]], understood the meaning which prompted him to suspect Notsil and contact the [[New Republic Intelligence Service]].

